SpecRelay — LICENSE STATUS: UNDECIDED (this is NOT a license grant)

This file is a deliberate placeholder. It is NOT a software license and grants
NO rights. No open-source license has been chosen for SpecRelay yet.

Why there is no LICENSE file
----------------------------
Choosing a license is a decision that requires explicit human authority. The
SDD 0086 task that prepared SpecRelay for standalone extraction is not permitted
to select a license on the project's behalf or to invent legal authority. Since
no explicit human license decision exists in the repository or task inputs, a
final `LICENSE` file cannot be added yet, and this placeholder records the gap
honestly instead of guessing.

Candidate licenses (options only — NOT applied)
-----------------------------------------------
A maintainer may later choose one of the following. Recording them here as
candidates does not apply any of them:

  - Apache-2.0
  - MIT

What a maintainer should do
---------------------------
1. Make an explicit license decision.
2. Add the corresponding `LICENSE` file with the full license text.
3. Update the "License" section of README.md accordingly.
4. Delete this LICENSE.TODO file.

Until those steps are done, do not assume any usage, distribution, or
modification rights beyond viewing the source.
